\section{Service integration}

\subsection{Motivation and goals}
The following section discusses key components of a conceptual design aiming towards the implementation of the previously described model into a full-fledged service to assist infrastructure managers in monitoring and planning operations.
This objective in mind, we intend to deploy our methods on a municipality/local district of Kobe city in order to investigate its applicability and obtain a proof-of-concept for the local administrators.
During the course of realizing such a deployment, several essential questions, concerning the functionality of the project, have arisen, such as:
\begin{itemize}
\item how to efficiently collect data to exhaustively cover the target road network; 
\item how to deal with errors and uncertainties in the model output; 
\item how to integrate the extracted intelligence into existing processes to derive feasible action plans.
\end{itemize}

Considering these questions, we have needed to define a set of fundamental goals/requirements towards our system to ensure its smooth and economic implementability, for example
\begin{itemize}
\item to methodically acquire an exhaustive and accurately geo-localized imaging of the pavement of the road network;
\item to extract a multitude of geo-localized defects using our model;
\item to integrate the images and the output of the model into a GIS system for manual operators to assess errors and uncertainties;
\item to propose the generation of a proof-of-concept automatic action plan, concerning the output of the model, an objective and economic constraints;
\item to minimize the acquisition cost to make it widely accessible. 
\end{itemize}


